## Summary: US-001 PDF Parser Unicode Fix

**Problem:** The PDF parser in `src/lib/pdf-parser.ts` uses Chinese characters directly in regex patterns, which can cause Unicode matching issues.

**Solution:** Replace Chinese characters with Unicode escape sequences in regex patterns.

### Required Changes to `src/lib/pdf-parser.ts`:

Replace the following characters in regex patterns:

| Character | Unicode Escape |
|-----------|----------------|
| 节 | `\u8282` |
| ☆ | `\u2606` |
| 周 | `\u5468` |
| 一 | `\u4e00` |
| 二 | `\u4e8c` |
| 三 | `\u4e09` |
| 四 | `\u56db` |
| 五 | `\u4e94` |
| 六 | `\u516d` |
| 日 | `\u65e5` |
| 天 | `\u5929` |
| 单周 | `\u5355\u5468` |
| 双周 | `\u53cc\u5468` |

### Key regex pattern changes:

```javascript
// Before (may fail Unicode matching):
const coursePattern = /☆(.+?)\s*\[([^\]]*)\]\s*星期 ([一二三四五六日天]+)\s+(\d+)-(\d+) 节\s+(.+?)\s+(.+)/g;

// After (reliable Unicode matching):
const coursePattern = /\u2606(.+?)\s*\[([^\]]*)\]\s*星期 ([\u4e00-\u5929]+)\s+(\d+)-(\d+)\u8282\s+(.+?)\s+(.+)/g;
```

